4) Actionable Mining Optimizations
   A. Monotonic Scanning:
      If miner scans S = {W, W-1, W-2, ...} (downward),
      this is already optimal for the exponential model.
      AVOID: Alternating (0, +1, -1, +2, -2, ...) - SUBOPTIMAL

   B. Priority Sampling:
      Sample offsets from exponential distribution with λ
      λ ≈ 0.000941 (average across stable range)
      Bias search toward small d (near left boundary)

